Why does adding `where` below confuse Julia (and some developers, CC <@U67431ELR>)?:
```julia&gt; struct X{A, B}
       end

julia&gt; const Y{B, A} = X{A, B} where {A, B}
X{A,B} where B where A

julia&gt; const Z{B, A} = X{A, B} where {B, A}
X{A,B} where A where B

julia&gt; Y{2, 1} # confused
X{2,1}

julia&gt; Z{2, 1} # as expected
X{1,2}```

elements.text:
julia> struct X{A, B}
       end

julia> const Y{B, A} = X{A, B} where {A, B}
X{A,B} where B where A

julia> const Z{B, A} = X{A, B} where {B, A}
X{A,B} where A where B

julia> Y{2, 1} # confused
X{2,1}

julia> Z{2, 1} # as expected
X{1,2}
